```java
public static boolean isPowerOfThree(int n) {
    if (n < 0 || n > 0x7FFFFFFF) return false; // Invalid input range

    // Find the least significant set bit in n
    int numBits = Integer.numberOfLeadingZeros(n);

    // Use a binary search to find the power of three that is closest to n
    int lowerBound = 0;
    int upperBound = 31;
    int middle = (upperBound + lowerBound) >>> 1; // Calculate middle by shifting to make room for the sum
    while (lowerBound <= upperBound) {
        int sum = n << middle;
        if (sum == n) {
            // Found a power of three that is equal to n
            return true;
        } else if (sum < n) {
            lowerBound = middle + 1;
        } else {
            upperBound = middle - 1;
        }
        middle = (upperBound + lowerBound) >>> 1;
    }
    return false; // If we reach here, no power of three was found
}
```
This solution works by first finding the least significant set bit in the integer `n`. Then, it uses a binary search to find the closest power of three to `n`. If the binary search finds a power of three that is equal to `n`, the function returns true. Otherwise, it returns false.

